article.description: Darius Dawkins hit a pair of 3-pointers in the final 3:35 to allow Jacksonville to hold off Marist, 69-68 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Dawkins' 3s allows Jacksonville to hold off Marist, 69-68
article.linkText: Dawkins' 3s allows Jacksonville to hold off Marist, 69-68
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Darius Dawkins hit a pair of 3-pointers in the final 3:35 to allow Jacksonville to hold off Marist, 69-68 Tuesday night. Dawkins second trey gave the Dolphins a three-point lead, 69-66 with 2:05 to play, but Jacksonville did not score again. Khallid Hart pulled Marist within one, 69-68 with 1:18 left, but missed a layup with 43 seconds left for the lead. Isaiah Lamb gave Marist the lead with 5:32 left on a 3-pointer on a feed from Kristinn Palsson and Brian Parker did it again with 4:31 left on a three-point play to make it 62-61. Marcel White hit 4 of 4 from beyond the arc and finished with 20 points to lead Jacksonville (6-8), with Kori Babineaux adding 17 points and Dawkins 12. Hart finished with 21 points to lead the Red Foxes, hitting 3 of 7 from long range. Parker added 16 points and Lamb contributed 11.
